THE father of a 10-year-old boy found floating at Umlalazi River on Tuesday believes that his son was murdered before being thrown into the river.Sibongakonke Mpungose left home on Sunday to play with his friends, but he never returned.He was a grade 4 pupil at KwaMondi Primary School.His dad, Mcebo (40), from Kwamfana Village near King Dinuzulu kasi, said he strongly believes that his son was killed by someone from the village.&ldquo;He did not throw himself in the river . . . he was kidnapped. I&rsquo;m saying this because the villagers who found his clothes near the river saw two sets of footprints. One of them were those of my son and the other set belonged to an older person,&rdquo; said Mcebo.He said he moved to the area three years ago and has no enemies.&ldquo;My son had open wounds on his body. I believe the killer killed and undressed him before throwing the body into the river. &ldquo;The killer wanted us to believe that he had drowned.&ldquo;This person has caused me a lot of pain and suffering. The manner in which my son died has left a huge hole in my heart,&rdquo; said the sad dad. KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said: &ldquo;An inquest docket was opened at Eshowe Police Station after a 10-year-old boy was found floating in Umlalazi River on Tuesday. &ldquo;Circumstances surrounding the incident are still being investigated.&rdquo;